<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/704688-i-have-a-question-about-a-certain-aspect">I have a question about a certain aspect of this book, namely the magic. In the description it says something about &quot;old-world magic&quot;. I can guess what it means, but I&#39;m slightly scared it&#39;ll turn out to be about a spellcasting Merlin - like in a Lord of the Rings novel or something. Is this the case? Or is it more of a real, genuine account of the age of Arthur (I hope so!)?Thanks!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_704688'><a id="like_count_community_question_704688" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/704688?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F68520.The_Winter_King">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/704688-i-have-a-question-about-a-certain-aspect">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/704688-i-have-a-question-about-a-certain-aspect">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

