<div id="review_2167190437" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2167190437" />
    <a title="Manisha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29882975-manisha"><img alt="Manisha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1499920903p2/29882975.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2167190437?book_show_action=true">Nov 21, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Manisha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Manisha" href="/user/show/29882975-manisha">Manisha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780140231861" href="/book/show/826595.The_Winter_King">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">fans of Arthur. </span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29882975-manisha?shelf=genre-historical-fiction">genre-historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29882975-manisha?shelf=series-trilogy">series-trilogy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29882975-manisha?shelf=genre-retellings">genre-retellings</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/29882975-manisha?shelf=pages-501-1000">pages-501-1000</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2167190437" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15597838948839156190"><b>Actual review:</b> 4.5<br/><br/><i>“But fate, as Merlin always taught us, is inexorable. Life is a jest of the Gods, Merlin liked to claim, and there is no justice. You must learn to laugh, he once told me, or else you&apos;ll just weep yourself to death.”</i><br/><br/>This was absolutely fantastic! <br/><br/>We meet the same characters we’ve known through countless stories, re-imaginings and movies, and we see them in a world based in reality. The concept is one that many have attempted but none have pulled off satisfactorily…. until now.<br/><br/>T</span>
  <span id="freeText15597838948839156190" style="display:none"><b>Actual review:</b> 4.5<br /><br /><i>“But fate, as Merlin always taught us, is inexorable. Life is a jest of the Gods, Merlin liked to claim, and there is no justice. You must learn to laugh, he once told me, or else you'll just weep yourself to death.”</i><br /><br />This was absolutely fantastic! <br /><br />We meet the same characters we’ve known through countless stories, re-imaginings and movies, and we see them in a world based in reality. The concept is one that many have attempted but none have pulled off satisfactorily…. until now.<br /><br />The Winter King by Bernard Cornwell is not a story about Arthur Pendragon who pulls a sword from a stone and becomes the perfect ruler with his sidekick Merlin. The story is about Arthur, a general who tries to unite England during the Dark Ages. The story feels historic, realistic, gritty and brilliant. <br /><br />I admit that I went into this book knowing nothing (it’s my chosen method of reading), so I was quite surprised by the level of importance religion played in this story. The discussion of Christianity feels like the most important fact to take away from this novel. So, if the discussion of religion bothers you, I would suggest you give this book a miss. As a result, even though this is a 'fantasy' series, it feels more like historical fiction. And the writing is impeccable and easy to follow. <br /><br />A quick warning to those who are about to delve into this world:<br /><br />Beware the first half of the book. The set up of the world seems a bit forced and it moves slowly compared to the rest of the book. If it wasn’t for the fact that it took me quite a while to get into the book, I would have given it five stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15597838948839156190" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


